@nalind PTAL

@Fodoj thanks for the PR.  Your thinking was very well thought out and articulated.  Thank you for that.  I understand the reasoning, but I still disagree with it, granted I may be a bit too sentimental here.  I'll get over my (probably demented) thoughts on the change, and I'll move forward.  

All that said, I would very much like to thank you for this contribution.  It was very well done and I truly appreciate your efforts and explanations.  To me, this is an excellent example of how OpenSource software development should go.  People expressing reasoned opinions and a final solution is created based on the discussions.

Cheers!   :champagne:
